Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': "--- a/Modules/_lsprof.c\n+++ b/Modules/_lsprof.c\n@@ -757,11 +757,26 @@\n flush_unmatched(ProfilerObject *pObj)\n {\n     while (pObj->currentProfilerContext) {\n         ProfilerContext *pContext = pObj->currentProfilerContext;\n         ProfilerEntry *profEntry= pContext->ctxEntry;\n+        /* Unlink pContext from freelist if it's there */\n+        if (pObj->freelistProfilerContext == pContext) {\n+            pObj->freelistProfilerContext = pContext->previous;\n+        } else {\n+            /* Otherwise, filter freelist to remove pContext if present */\n+            ProfilerContext **pp = &pObj->freelistProfilerContext;\n+            while (*pp && *pp != pContext)\n+                pp = &(*pp)->previous;\n+            if (*pp == pContext)\n+                *pp = pContext->previous;\n+        }\n         if (profEntry)\n             Stop(pObj, pContext, profEntry);\n         else\n             pObj->currentProfilerContext = pContext->previous;\n         PyMem_Free(pContext);\n     }\n+    pObj->freelistProfilerContext = NULL;\n }"}`
responded: Here’s the most critical detail from all attempts and code inspection:

**A context can be freed more than once because:**
- It may exist in both `currentProfilerContext` (the stack) and the freelist (`freelistProfilerContext`).
- The call to `flush_unmatched` in `profiler_dealloc` is followed by a call to `clearEntries`, which also attempts to free all remaining `freelistProfilerContext` entries—so doubly owned contexts get freed again.

**Best resolvable patch, matching CPython memory discipline:**  
- After freeing a context in `flush_unmatched`, if `freelistProfilerContext` points to that context, advance it.
- After the loop, set `freelistProfilerContext = NULL` so further teardown doesn't try to free already-freed contexts.

Let’s also ensure we only free pContext ONCE, and that the `clearEntries` logic doesn't conflict (since it will see freelist already set to NULL after `flush_unmatched`).

Here is a robust patch to implement this logic:

```diff
@@ -757,11 +757,18 @@
 flush_unmatched(ProfilerObject *pObj)
 {
     while (pObj->currentProfilerContext) {
         ProfilerContext *pContext = pObj->currentProfilerContext;
         ProfilerEntry *profEntry= pContext->ctxEntry;
+        /* Unlink pContext from freelist if it's there */
+        if (pObj->freelistProfilerContext == pContext) {
+            pObj->freelistProfilerContext = pContext->previous;
+        } else {
+            /* Otherwise, filter freelist to remove pContext if present */
+            ProfilerContext **pp = &pObj->freelistProfilerContext;
+            while (*pp && *pp != pContext)
+                pp = &(*pp)->previous;
+            if (*pp == pContext)
+                *pp = pContext->previous;
+        }
         if (profEntry)
             Stop(pObj, pContext, profEntry);
         else
             pObj->currentProfilerContext = pContext->previous;
         PyMem_Free(pContext);
     }
+    pObj->freelistProfilerContext = NULL;
 }
```

